### Core Services

|name|function
|router|
  - gzip support
  - https TLS encryption (SSL certificate, autoreload)
  - TODO http/2
  - http â†’ https redirection
|ci|
  - process receives github/gitlab webhooks
  - updates (pulls) repos on master branch change
  - compiles changed scripts
  - operates supervisor
|dashboard|
  - web frontend
  - backend is facade for the other services
|supervisor|
  - TODO resource limiting
  - process (re)starting
|log|
  - central logging
|TODO monitor|
  - monitor processes
  - twitch processes

### Config / Add Service

- â†‘.config/config.json :

  ```
  {
    "env": {â€¦},
    "processes": {â€¦},
    "webhooks": {â€¦}
  }
  ```
- every service and every hook must be restartable at any time (stateless)

|
|`env`|
  variables that can be used in the rest of this configuration with `${var}`
|`processes`|
  ```
  "infoaghh": {
    "script": "../infoaghh/main.js",
    "cwd": "../infoaghh",
    "args": ["::1", "${infoagport}"]
  }
  ```

  - `cwd` optional
  - `args` can be any JSON object
|`webhooks`|
  ```
  "infoaghh": {
    "token": "abc123",
    "path": "../infoaghh",
    "commands": "npm install\nlsc -c"
  }
  ```

  - set webhook path to `https://[ci root url]/webhook/infoaghh`
  - path must lead to a git repo
  - process-scripts that are updated are restarted

### Interfaces

|name|interface
|router|
  - first cli argument (`JSON.stringify`)
  - ```
    {
      port: routerport,
      http_redirect: "7080->#routerport",
      routes: ['localhost(:[0-9]+)?/admin': dashboardport],
      host: '127.0.0.1' (default '::1')
    }
    ```
|ci|
  - first cli argument is path to config file

  |HTTP
  |* `/webhook/[hookname]`|requires header 'x-gitlab-token' or 'x-hub-signature'
  |* `/webhook/[hookname]/restart`|doesn't require auth
  |* `/ls`
  |* `/start/[proc]`
  |* `/stop/[proc]`
  |GET `/config`
  |PUT `/config`
|cli (frontend)|
  - frontend interface to ci and log (see graphic)
  - â””â–ªcli lsâ†µ
  - â””â–ªcli start [name]â†µ
  - â””â–ªcli stop [name]â†µ
  - â””â–ªcli restart [name]â†µ
  - â””â–ªcli log [name]â†µ
    - âœ” managed from â†‘cli.ls for â†‘ci.ls
      - âœ” log for â†‘ci.ls viewable
    - âœ” managed from â†‘ci.ls for rest
      - âœ” â†‘ci_state.json already used
      - âœ” hiding implementation details from â†‘cli.ls
|dashboard|
  - replaces login to server (ideally)

  |HTTP
  |`*`|`?token=xxx` required
  |`* /`|serve web frontend
  |`* /ls`|list of processes and hooks|```
    ps: [{name,status,pid,ports}, â€¦],
    hooks: [{name,lines:[{command,output,duration,code},â€¦]}, â€¦]
    ```
  |`* /proc/[name]/start`|
  |`* /proc/[name]/stop`|
  |`* /proc/[name]/restart`|
  |`GET /config`|get cli JSON argument|JSON (see â†‘config.json template)
  |`PUT /config`|set cli JSON argument|JSON (see â†‘config.json template)
  |`* /log[/proc]`|see [adabru-log](./Log)

  - first cli argument (`JSON.stringify`)
  - ```
    {
      dashboardport: dashboardport,
      ciport: ciport,
      logbackendport: logbackendport,
      token: "abc123"
    }
    ```
|logserver|
  see [adabru-log](./Log)

### Error Handling

Restart processes or see log at https://[host/base]/admin/ or with â””â–ªcliâ†µ.

If `router`, `log`, `dashboard` or `ci` are affected, use â””â–ªcliâ†µ.

If services have unexpected behaviour, use â””â–ªcurlâ†µ

Force stop with â””â–ªkill -9 [pid]â†µ,

